<L N="185">A while, to &s;ave the capital of Greece,</L>
<L>Superb in &s;tructure, long-di&s;puted prize</L>
<L>Between Minerva and the god of &s;eas,</L>
<L>Of eloquence the parent, &s;ource of arts,</L>
<L>Fair &s;eat of freedom! Open are the ga&s;es,</L>
<L N="190">The dwellings mute, all de&s;olate the &s;treets,</L>
